  "prompt": "Are there any TV series similar to How to Get Away with Murder?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several TV series that share similarities with *How to Get Away with Murder* in terms of intense drama, legal intrigue, mysterious plotlines, and complex characters. Here are some recommendations:\n\n### Legal Dramas with Thrilling Twists:\n1. **Suits**  \n   - Focuses on a talented college dropout who becomes a lawyer at a prestigious law firm, blending legal drama with sharp wit and personal dynamics.  \n\n2. **The Good Wife**  \n   - A legal drama that delves into the personal and professional life of a lawyer returning to her career after a political scandal involving her husband.  \n\n3. **Damages**  \n   - A psychological thriller centered around a ruthless lawyer and her protegee, featuring intricate plotting and morally ambiguous characters.  \n\n### Mystery and Crime Series:\n4. **Scandal**  \n   - Created by Shonda Rhimes (like *HTGAWM*), this series follows a crisis manager navigating political scandals, featuring high-stakes drama and shocking twists.  \n\n5. **Big Little Lies**  \n   - A gripping mix of mystery and drama, focusing on a group of women entangled in a web of secrets and lies.  \n\n6. **The Undoing**  \n   - A psychological thriller about a therapist whose life unravels after a violent death, with plenty of suspense and moral ambiguity.  \n\n### Thrillers with Complex Characters:\n7. **Killing Eve**  \n   - A cat-and-mouse game between a MI5 agent and a psychopathic assassin, filled with dark humor and intense drama.  \n\n8. **Ozark**  \n   - A family gets caught up in money laundering and criminal schemes, featuring high tension and morally complex characters.  \n\n9. **The Night Of**  \n   - A miniseries exploring the legal system through the story of a young man accused of murder, with a focus on moral ambiguity and societal issues.  \n\n### Dark and Twisted Dramas:\n10. **Revenge**  \n    - A woman plots to avenge her father\u2019s wrongful conviction, filled with twists, deception, and high-stakes drama.  \n\n11. **Pretty Little Liars**  \n    - A group of friends navigates secrets, lies, and a mysterious antagonist, with plenty of suspense and drama.  \n\n12. **Why Women Kill** A darkly comedic drama explores the lives of women across different decades, all connected by themes of betrayal and murder.  \n\nThese series share elements of suspense, morally complex characters, and intricate storytelling, making them great options if you enjoyed *How to Get Away with Murder*.",
